# About

I'm an investigative reporter and data journalist, which means my job is to sift through large datasets and records to find and tell stories in the public interest. I often use programming languages to help with this work.

I currently work for the [Pittsburgh Post-Gazette](https://www.post-gazette.com/), where I have reported on a range of issues including housing, air safety and mining. Before joining the Post-Gazette, I covered campaign finance and lobbying for [OpenSecrets](https://www.opensecrets.org/), a nonprofit that tracks the influence of money in U.S. politics. I also freelanced for the [Virginia Center for Investigative Journalism](https://vcij.org/). 

I studied English literature at Virginia Commonwealth University and later graduated with a master's degree in investigative journalism from Arizona State University. Between then, I taught high school and spent two years in Armenia with the U.S. Peace Corps, teaching English as a foreign language. 

I grew up outside Richmond, Virginia, but I was born in a small town in Qu√©bec, Canada.

